    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"## Interpretation Guide\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"### Effect Size Interpretation (Cohen's d):\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- **Small effect**: |d| ≈ 0.2\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- **Medium effect**: |d| ≈ 0.5\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- **Large effect**: |d| ≈ 0.8\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"### Key Observations:\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"1. **Sustainability** showed significant improvement across all three models (GPT-5, Gemini, Deepseek)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"   - This suggests the calibration was most effective for the sustainability dimension\\n\",\n",
    "    \"   - Effect sizes ranged from small to medium (d = 0.29 to 0.49)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"2. **Deepseek** showed the most comprehensive improvements:\\n\",\n",
    "    \"   - Significant changes in relevance (d = 0.57, medium-to-large effect)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"   - Significant changes in sustainability (d = 0.49, medium effect)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"   - Significant changes in diversity (d = 0.27, small effect)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"3. **Popularity Balance** remained largely unchanged across all models\\n\",\n",
    "    \"   - This dimension may be more resistant to calibration\\n\",\n",
    "    \"   - Or the calibration approach may need refinement for this dimension\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"4. **Statistical Test Agreement**:\\n\",\n",
    "    \"   - Both parametric (paired t-test) and non-parametric (Wilcoxon) tests generally agree\\n\",\n",
    "    \"   - This provides robust evidence for the observed effects\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
